some of my passion, it's really hard for me

00:01:13.686 --> 00:01:15.886 align:middle
to devote a lot of my time and energy to it.

00:01:15.886 --> 00:01:20.666 align:middle
So that kind of made school a struggle, because
there was always a balance between focusing

00:01:20.666 --> 00:01:25.076 align:middle
and being motivated on something that
didn't necessarily kind of captivate me.

00:01:25.336 --> 00:01:29.706 align:middle
So that's a skill that I had to develop was,
you know, just because I'm not interested

00:01:29.706 --> 00:01:31.606 align:middle
in this doesn't mean I shouldn't
work hard for it.

00:01:31.766 --> 00:01:35.856 align:middle
I think what was cool with my parents was they
actually helped me understand my disability

00:01:35.856 --> 00:01:36.936 align:middle
at a scientific level.

00:01:37.276 --> 00:01:41.866 align:middle
Sometimes when you act different than other
people, that can make you feel really strange.

00:01:42.246 --> 00:01:45.906 align:middle
And what my parents just let me know is that
it was just a difference in my brain chemistry.

00:01:45.906 --> 00:01:49.456 align:middle
It didn't make me a bad person
or an unintelligent person,

00:01:49.726 --> 00:01:51.476 align:middle
it just made me act a little bit differently.

00:01:51.546 --> 00:01:53.816 align:middle
And as soon as I started
to learn more about that,

00:01:54.156 --> 00:01:56.186 align:middle
I was able to accept myself a little bit more.

00:01:56.186 --> 00:01:57.086 align:middle
So that really helped.

00:01:57.686 --> 00:02:01.976 align:middle
I think high expectations is interesting for
both the parent, and then also as an individual.

00:02:02.776 --> 00:02:04.876 align:middle
Sometimes if you're not succeeding in school,

00:02:04.876 --> 00:02:07.516 align:middle
it's really easy for your
expectations to change for yourself.

00:02:07.876 --> 00:02:11.616 align:middle
And I think the role of a parent is
to really help you keep those us.

00:02:12.016 --> 00:02:15.966 align:middle
So sometimes a parent can really help
someone see a future for yourself

00:02:15.966 --> 00:02:18.286 align:middle
that you currently can't see
because you're really struggling.

00:02:18.686 --> 00:02:22.066 align:middle
So my parents I think always really
helped me keep my eye on the ball.

00:02:22.526 --> 00:02:27.466 align:middle
And something that was really important that
they told me is that school is the only time

00:02:27.466 --> 00:02:29.396 align:middle
in your life where you have
to be good at everything.

00:02:29.776 --> 00:02:30.746 align:middle
You have to be good at math.

00:02:30.796 --> 00:02:31.776 align:middle
You have to be good at writing.

00:02:31.776 --> 00:02:33.516 align:middle
You have to be good at sports.

00:02:33.766 --> 00:02:35.806 align:middle
And it's really not like that in the real world.

00:02:35.806 --> 00:02:38.676 align:middle
The real world is where you
find hey what am I good at?

00:02:38.746 --> 00:02:39.776 align:middle
What motivates me?

00:02:40.056 --> 00:02:44.006 align:middle
And how can I bring that to a job,
to a hobby, and that's something

00:02:44.006 --> 00:02:45.476 align:middle
that they really helped me keep in mind.

00:02:45.476 --> 00:02:47.676 align:middle
And that was a big motivator going forward.

00:02:48.006 --> 00:02:52.486 align:middle
So I was fortunate enough to go to college,
and college, kind of like I was saying earlier,

00:02:52.486 --> 00:02:54.826 align:middle
is where you really get to
explore what interests you.

00:02:55.246 --> 00:02:58.216 align:middle
And in college I became fascinated
with technology

00:02:58.296 --> 00:03:00.376 align:middle
and how people interact with technology.

00:03:00.796 --> 00:03:04.886 align:middle
So when I graduated I still had that passion
of looking at technology, how people interact

00:03:04.886 --> 00:03:07.096 align:middle
with it, how technology benefits people.

00:03:07.436 --> 00:03:11.806 align:middle
And I saw this job as a really cool opportunity
to give back, learn a lot about people,

00:03:11.946 --> 00:03:14.566 align:middle
how they interact with technology,
and I'm having a lot of fun

00:03:14.566 --> 00:03:16.346 align:middle
and kind of growing each day with it.

00:03:16.596 --> 00:03:20.046 align:middle
So that's kind of something that really
motivated me to get into this field.

00:03:20.266 --> 00:03:23.466 align:middle
