look at is what are your strengths.

00:03:23.556 --> 00:03:26.666 align:middle
That's something that every
successful person, you know,

00:03:26.666 --> 00:03:29.186 align:middle
quotes disability or not, has to ask themselves.

00:03:29.556 --> 00:03:33.026 align:middle
So if you're in high school, I think it's
your job to really think about you know,

00:03:33.096 --> 00:03:35.976 align:middle
when I wake up every day, what
do I want to bring to this world?

00:03:36.366 --> 00:03:38.256 align:middle
And that's where you look at your strengths.

00:03:38.256 --> 00:03:40.136 align:middle
So when you wake up, is it your creativity?

00:03:40.456 --> 00:03:42.326 align:middle
Is it the way you interact with people?

00:03:42.326 --> 00:03:44.346 align:middle
Is it kind of some of your science smarts?

00:03:44.346 --> 00:03:49.276 align:middle
Really discover what it is that excites and
that you feel really positive and good about

00:03:49.566 --> 00:03:51.666 align:middle
and kind of push and pursue that thing.

00:03:51.956 --> 00:03:55.616 align:middle
Because a lot of people in life can, you
know, just take any job or do anything.

00:03:55.616 --> 00:03:58.586 align:middle
But I think the people that are really
successful and happy find things

00:03:58.926 --> 00:04:01.276 align:middle
that really connects with them
and really motivates them.

00:04:01.276 --> 00:04:03.906 align:middle
So even at high school you
can start to think about that.

00:04:03.906 --> 00:04:07.436 align:middle
Because that's going to really help
predict those next steps in your life.

